    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-01-24T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-01-24T19:00:00-05:00" n="151"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">399.10–<gloss target="#t_UPU1">UPU</gloss>/1–2451:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Egypt</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-01-24T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 24, 1951—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>711. For Redding. <gloss target="#t_reurtel1">Reurtel</gloss> 769 Jan 24. In
                    event US motion defeated and Fr compromise comes to vote agree you shld vote
                    against but not lobby or speak against. You shld of course strongly oppose
                    Soviet motion. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> considers use secret ballot
                    question this kind undesirable precedent and in any event seriously doubts
                    beneficial effect its use. Therefore, you shld not make motion use secret
                    ballot; if such motion made by other Del you shld abstain. <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> suggests you urge Brit Rep telephone <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> and attempt get authorization abstain or
                    support US motion in light of recent highest level talks between two govts on
                    China problems.<note n="1" xml:id="d151fn1">Refers presumably to a meeting on
                        the evening of January 23 of British Ambassador Franks “with Secretary and
                        other <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> officers for discussion
                        Korean-UN problem.” (Telegram <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 3512
                        to London, January 24, 7 p. m., 795.00/1–2451). For documentation on the
                        Korean War, see <ref target="frus1951v07p1">volume <hi rend="smallcaps"
                                >vii</hi>
                        </ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
